Extra requirements for applications for public procurement will be excluded by law
The legislation can establish comprehensive requirements for applications for participation in procurement.
In the autumn session at the plenary session of the State Duma, it is planned to consider in the second reading a bill that establishes requirements for the content and composition of an application for participation in the procurement, which can only be participants in small and medium-sized businesses.
Amendments are made by the government to the law "On the procurement of goods, works, services by certain types of legal entities".
The bill was developed in pursuance of the roadmap for the implementation of the Strategy for the Development of Small and Medium-Sized Enterprises in the Russian Federation until 2030, approved by the government.
It provides for the preparation of a draft law on an exhaustive list of documents that customers have the right to demand as part of the application from the participants in the procurement - small and medium-sized businesses.
And also - about the list of requirements to these documents.
To date, the law "On the procurement of goods, works, services by certain types of legal entities" frameworks regulates the procurement activities of certain types of legal entities.
Requirements for the content, form, registration and composition of the application for participation in the procurement are established by customers independently in the procurement documentation.
“As a result, customers establish excessive requirements for the content, registration of the application, the mandatory availability of certificates, certificates, extracts, the period of receipt of which in the authorized bodies is comparable to the deadline for submitting applications, which leads to the impossibility of participation in such purchase and reduction of the number of participants in the procurement”, – stated in the explanatory note to the bill.
The new bill provides for the establishment of an exhaustive list of documents that customers have the right to demand as part of the application from procurement participants who are small and medium-sized businesses.
“The adoption of the document will eliminate the arbitrary establishment by customers of the requirements for the composition and content of applications of participants who are small and medium-sized businesses,” the explanatory note says.
