Degtyarev was surprised by the information about the purchase of gas "Sakhalin-1" for dollars
Acting Governor of the Khabarovsk Territory Mikhail Degtyarev on Sunday, July 26, during a meeting with residents of the Soviet Havana, was surprised that the region is buying Sakhalin gas produced by the American company Exxon Neftegas, for dollars.
American gas is contracted in dollars until 2025.
“Honestly, I didn’t know that, and I’m not at such a knockout because of this information.
I did not even have an idea that this is still possible in 2020 in Russia, ”RIA Novosti quotes him as saying.
Degtyarev noted that this issue was discussed with the head of the Ministry of Energy of Russia Alexander Novak during his visit to Khabarovsk on July 24.
Also, the acting governor stressed that by 2025, Gazprom is moving to supply Russian thermal power plants and capacities, which means that Russian gas purchased in rubles “at normal prices” will be used.
The Sakhalin-1 project is implemented through a production sharing agreement, where the project operator with a share of 30% is Exxon Neftegas Ltd, another 20% for Rosneft, and the Japanese Sodeco has 30% and the Indian ONG-200%.
The Khabarovsk Territory has been buying gas from this project since 2005.
