A woman threw her husband’s body into a pit and poured concrete near Belfast
In the Belgorod region, a woman confessed to the murder of her husband, whom she dumped in a pit with waste and poured concrete, according to the website of the regional department of the Investigative Committee of the Russian Federation.
It is noted that the suspect lived in marriage with the murdered since 1999.
In recent years, the husband began to abuse alcohol and after another quarrel, the woman decided to kill.
“When the husband fell asleep, the suspect tied his arms and legs, put a plastic bag on his head and crushed a pillow.
When the husband stopped showing signs of life, wrapped the body in a carpet, took it to the yard and hid in a cesspool.
The next day she called a concrete mixer and poured the pit with concrete,” the department said.
The woman later reported that her husband was missing.
Relatives of the deceased appealed to the police, who opened the pit and extracted the body.
The investigation intends to ask the court to arrest the suspect.
The investigation of the criminal case is ongoing.
